d 'XTMUNITROOT': module providing fixed-T panel unit root tests with missing values
d
d      xtmunitroot implements the fixed-T panel unit root tests of
d Harris and Tzavalis (1999) and Karavias and Tzavalis (2014),	 
d extended to unbalanced panels with missing values exactly as in
d Karavias, Tzavalis and Zhang (2022). These tests are designed   
d for panels with a large number of cross-section units N and a
d small, fixed number of time periods T.    The model is an AR(1)
d panel, u(i,t) = rho*u(i,t-1) + e(i,t), and the test is	H0:
d rho = 1 (every panel has a unit root) vs H1: rho < 1
d (stationary).    The pooled fixed-effects estimator of rho is
d inconsistent for fixed T (the Hurwicz-Nickell bias), so it is
d bias-corrected and	the resulting statistic is asymptotically
d standard normal as N -> infinity:	   z = (rho_hat - bias - 1)
d / sqrt(V/N) -> N(0,1) under H0.    Because rho_hat is biased
d downward, the bias is negative; under stationarity z is large and
d negative, so the unit-root null is	rejected in the lower tail. d
d KW:  panel data
d KW: panel unit root
d KW: fixed-T
d KW: missing values
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260629
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f xtmunitroot.ado
f xtmunitroot.sthlp
f xtmunitroot_example.do
